                    <note xml:lang="en" type="abstract" corresp="http://syriaca.org/persons http://syriaca.org/authors">
                        <quote source="#bib9-1">Bp. of <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/182">Seleucia-Ctesiphon</placeName> and martyr. Shemʿon was probably the
                            immediate successor of Papa bar ʿAggai (d. between 327 and 335), but
                            nothing is known about his tenure as bp. prior to his arrest.</quote>
                    </note>
                    <note xml:lang="en" type="abstract" resp="http://syriaca.org" corresp="http://syriaca.org/q http://syriaca.org/saints">In hagiography: <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/9">Simeon bar Sabbaʿe</persName> is
                        commemorated as bishop of <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/182">Seleucia-Ctesiphon</placeName> and one of the earliest and most famous
                        of the Persian Martyrs. He was from <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/415">Susa</placeName> and was the
                        archdeacon of Catholicos Papa bar ʿAggai whom he succeeded in 329. He was
                        imprisoned at Karka d-Ledan and was decapitated.</note>
